      "description": "Available is a driver-focused E92 M3 featuring the high-revving S65B40 naturally aspirated V8 and a precise six-speed manual transmission. This specimen maintains its mechanical integrity with recent preventative maintenance including rod bearing replacement and new throttle actuators. The chassis retains its composure through Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and the M Variable Differential Lock, providing exceptional lateral grip and turn-in response. The individual throttle bodies are synchronized perfectly, offering the immediate throttle mapping characteristic of this 8,400 RPM power plant. While the finish shows minor road rash consistent with enthusiast use, the subframe bushings and hydraulic steering rack remain tight and leak-free. A mechanically robust example of the last naturally aspirated M3.",
